abstract: What’s driving GOOG higher. Could it be nothing?
snippet: What’s driving GOOG higher. Could it be nothing?
lead_paragraph: When before Google reported second quarter earnings on July 19, its shares closed at $548.59, just a few dollars short of an all-time high. But during its earnings report Google said that its expenses for the quarter were a bit higher than Wall Street expected. That spooked investors who sent Google’s shares tumbling, cutting their value in after hours trading by $42.
